{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/connect-four-coding-challenge","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"0e26db69-a50f-59fc-b954-939a1f33465d","html":"<p>I got a coding challenge from an E-commerce company in the bay area. This was for a Frontend developer position. The challenge was simply to develop a connect four game using only HTML, CSS and Javascript. This is the most common board game.</p>\n<p>It is a two-player connection game in which the players first choose a color and then take turns dropping one colored disc from the top into a seven-column, six-row vertically suspended grid. The pieces fall straight down, occupying the lowest available space within the column. The objective of the game is to be the first to form a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal line of four of oneâ€™s own discs. Connect Four is a solved game. The first player can always win by playing the right moves. [Source Wikipedia]</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/7be202fb8678db23d6322dd618a6231a/b4294/connect-four-game.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/blog/static/7be202fb8678db23d6322dd618a6231a/8ac56/connect-four-game.webp 240w,\n/blog/static/7be202fb8678db23d6322dd618a6231a/d3be9/connect-four-game.webp 480w,\n/blog/static/7be202fb8678db23d6322dd618a6231a/e88ff/connect-four-game.webp 600w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/blog/static/7be202fb8678db23d6322dd618a6231a/09b79/connect-four-game.jpg 240w,\n/blog/static/7be202fb8678db23d6322dd618a6231a/7cc5e/connect-four-game.jpg 480w,\n/blog/static/7be202fb8678db23d6322dd618a6231a/b4294/connect-four-game.jpg 600w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/blog/static/7be202fb8678db23d6322dd618a6231a/b4294/connect-four-game.jpg\"\n            alt=\"Connect 4 Image\"\n            title=\"Connect 4 Image\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The interesting part was to develop this game within 4 hours from scratch. I had to code the game in HackerEarth IDE which does not allow copying of content. It would be much faster if I could code in my IDE and then copy it to HackerEarth IDE. I took less than 3 hours to complete the game and it came out good.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 459px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/blog/static/bfc63e5dbcdb7b2898987e431e7539e2/48711/sukruth-connect-four-game.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 102.91666666666669%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/blog/static/bfc63e5dbcdb7b2898987e431e7539e2/8ac56/sukruth-connect-four-game.webp 240w,\n/blog/static/bfc63e5dbcdb7b2898987e431e7539e2/25604/sukruth-connect-four-game.webp 459w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 459px) 100vw, 459px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/blog/static/bfc63e5dbcdb7b2898987e431e7539e2/8ff5a/sukruth-connect-four-game.png 240w,\n/blog/static/bfc63e5dbcdb7b2898987e431e7539e2/48711/sukruth-connect-four-game.png 459w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 459px) 100vw, 459px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/blog/static/bfc63e5dbcdb7b2898987e431e7539e2/48711/sukruth-connect-four-game.png\"\n            alt=\"Game Screenshot\"\n            title=\"Game Screenshot\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>You can check this git repo for my code. This is a better version than the one I coded for the challenge.<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/sukruthmk/Connect-Four\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/sukruthmk/Connect-Four</a></p>\n<p>Also, check out the game here. I hope you like it.<br>\n<a href=\"http://sukruthmk.com/Connect-Four/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">http://sukruthmk.com/Connect-Four/</a></p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/connect-four-coding-challenge","tagSlugs":["/tag/blogging/","/tag/game-development/","/tag/java-script/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2018-11-12T07:05:20.000Z","description":"My thoughts on developing a Connect Four game using JavaScript","tags":["Blogging","Game Development","JavaScript"],"title":"Connect Four Coding Challenge","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/connect-four-coding-challenge"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","825871152"]}